      {
        "id": "17",
        "title": "Implement Updated Auto-Poster Workflow",
        "description": "Rebuild the auto-poster pipeline to match the finalized E2E workflow in docs/auto-poster-workflow.md. Major changes: (1) Content Research Pipeline â€” module that reads Coda notes via MCP, pulls backtest reports from 192.168.1.11:5050, captures your own TradingView indicator signal screenshots, checks market events calendar. Outputs structured content brief. (2) Content Generation â€” update generate.ps1 for per-platform cadence: X 3 tweets/day + 2 threads/week, Reddit 2-3/week, LinkedIn 4/week Tue-Fri, Facebook 1/day. Voice: discovery-oriented, never claiming trading experience, emotion-first hooks. Cross-platform repurposing. (3) Review Dashboard â€” drafts grouped by platform, pillar tags, format labels, image previews, 1-day content buffer. (4) Posting Schedule â€” platform-specific times aligned to US hours. (5) Image/slideshow generation â€” visually striking, scroll-stopping, branded, mobile-first. (6) CTA rotation: month 1 = 100% value, month 2+ = 80/15/5. (7) Content series: Backtest Wednesday, Setup of the Week, One Thing I Learned This Week.",
        "details": "Reference docs/auto-poster-workflow.md for complete spec. This is a large task that should be broken into subtasks during implementation planning. Key files to modify: scripts/generate.ps1, scripts/post.py, scripts/review_dashboard.py, scripts/setup_scheduler.ps1, scripts/utils/image_generator.py. New modules needed: content research pipeline, market events calendar, content buffer manager.",
        "testStrategy": "",
        "status": "deferred",
        "dependencies": [],
        "priority": "high",
        "subtasks": [],
        "updatedAt": "2026-03-22T10:57:13.166Z"
      },
      {
        "id": "18",
        "title": "Test Run â€” Confirm Updated Workflow Works",
        "description": "End-to-end test of the updated auto-poster workflow. Run through the complete pipeline: content research â†’ generation â†’ review dashboard â†’ posting to all 4 active platforms (X, Reddit, LinkedIn, Facebook). Verify: (1) Content research pipeline correctly pulls from Coda notes, backtest reports, and your own indicator signal screenshots. (2) Generator produces correct volume per platform (X: 3 tweets, Reddit: 1 long-form, LinkedIn: 1 post, Facebook: 1 post). (3) Drafts appear correctly in review dashboard grouped by platform with pillar tags and image previews. (4) Approved drafts post at correct platform-specific times. (5) Content buffer logic works (1-day buffer). (6) Image generation produces visually striking, branded content. (7) Failure handling works (retry once, then move to failed). Fix any bugs found.",
        "details": "Test against real platforms. Use existing browser profiles. Check human behavior emulation still works. Verify draft lifecycle: review/ â†’ pending/ â†’ posted/ or failed/. Test with headless=false first to visually confirm.",
        "testStrategy": "",
        "status": "deferred",
        "dependencies": [
          "17"
        ],
        "priority": "high",
        "subtasks": [],
        "updatedAt": "2026-03-22T10:57:34.509Z"
      },
      {
        "id": "19",
        "title": "Account Warmup â€” Gradual Ramp-Up Per Platform",
        "description": "Execute the account warmup plan for all 4 platforms before going to full posting cadence. New accounts risk being flagged as spam if they go from 0 to full volume immediately. Warmup schedule: X (new account) â€” Week 1: 1 tweet/day + 10 replies/day, Week 2: 2 tweets/day + replies, Week 3+: full cadence (3/day + threads). Reddit â€” Weeks 1-2: comments only (3-5/day, no posts, build karma), Weeks 3-4: 1 post every few days, Month 2+: full cadence 2-3/week. LinkedIn (existing 9.5K connections) â€” no warmup needed, start at full cadence 4/week Tue-Fri. Facebook (existing but empty) â€” Week 1: 1 post every other day, Week 2+: 1/day. The auto-poster's posting frequency config should support a warmup mode that automatically escalates cadence week by week.",
        "details": "Implement warmup mode in the posting scheduler. Config should have a start_date per platform and automatically calculate which warmup week we're in. Cadence increases automatically â€” no manual intervention needed. Reference docs/auto-poster-workflow.md Account Warmup Plan section.",
        "testStrategy": "",
        "status": "deferred",
        "dependencies": [
          "18"
        ],
        "priority": "high",
        "subtasks": [],
        "updatedAt": "2026-03-22T10:57:42.172Z"
      },
      {
        "id": "20",
        "title": "Revamp Profiles â€” X, Reddit, LinkedIn, Facebook",
        "description": "Revamp all 4 platform profiles to align with the brand strategy before going live. X: Create new account with new email. Bio, banner, profile pic aligned with brand identity (helps people achieve financial freedom, not tool builder). Link to TradingView. Reddit: Update existing profile â€” bio, avatar. No self-promotion in bio, just establish credibility. LinkedIn: Revamp existing profile (9.5K connections) for US positioning. Update headline, about section, banner. Shift from Indian professional network to US-targeted trading education brand. Facebook: Set up empty profile â€” bio, cover photo, profile pic. All profiles must: hide age and location, use US-centric language, have consistent branding across platforms, link to TradingView where applicable.",
        "details": "Do this AFTER the 'I'm back' LinkedIn discussion since that post informs the LinkedIn profile revamp. Ensure consistent visual branding (colors, fonts, profile pic style) across all 4 platforms. Profile bios should reflect the 'helps people achieve financial freedom' positioning, not 'builds trading tools'.",
        "testStrategy": "",
        "status": "deferred",
        "dependencies": [
