      {
        "id": "21",
        "title": "Discuss 'I'm Back' LinkedIn Post Strategy",
        "description": "Plan the LinkedIn re-introduction post before profile revamps. User has 9.5K connections dormant for 1-2 years. LinkedIn's algorithm boosts posts from reactivated accounts, making this a high-impact first move. The post should: (1) Re-introduce who you are and what you've been building (without revealing age/location). (2) Tease what's coming â€” trading tools, education, free indicators. (3) Set the tone for future content â€” emotion-first, value-first, builder-educator positioning. (4) Include a soft CTA (follow for upcoming content). This post informs the LinkedIn profile revamp â€” the profile and the post must tell a coherent story. Discuss content, format, timing.",
        "details": "",
        "testStrategy": "",
        "status": "deferred",
        "dependencies": [
          "19"
        ],
        "priority": "high",
        "subtasks": [],
        "updatedAt": "2026-03-22T10:57:57.666Z"
      },
      {
        "id": "22",
        "title": "AI Video Generation for TikTok and Instagram",
        "description": "Research and integrate an AI video generation tool to produce short-form video content for TikTok and Instagram. Current slideshow-to-MP4 approach (Pillow image + Ken Burns zoom via moviepy) can't compete with native video content. TikTok's algorithm favors fresh accounts but only with real video. Instagram Reels require video too. Requirements: (1) Generate 15-30 second videos from text content (trading education, backtest results, market insights). (2) Branded visual style consistent with image generation. (3) Text-on-screen, transitions, background music. (4) Output formats: TikTok 1080x1920 vertical, Instagram Reels 1080x1920. Once video generation works, TikTok and Instagram become active platforms in the posting schedule (slots at 4:30 AM and 6:30 AM IST).",
        "details": "",
        "testStrategy": "",
        "status": "deferred",
        "dependencies": [],
        "priority": "medium",
        "subtasks": [],
        "updatedAt": "2026-03-22T10:58:05.294Z"
      },
      {
        "id": "23",
        "title": "Financial Newsletters/Articles as Content Source",
        "description": "Add curated financial newsletters and articles to the content research pipeline. The system reads 3-5 configured newsletter sources daily, extracts core insights, and rephrases them in the user's voice with their angle. NOT copy-paste â€” extract the insight, add perspective. This solves the 'content sounds fake because generator has no real knowledge' problem by grounding posts in real market analysis and expert commentary. Implementation: (1) Configure 3-5 newsletter sources (email subscriptions or RSS feeds). (2) Build a reader/parser that extracts key insights from each newsletter. (3) Feed extracted insights into the content research pipeline as additional content seeds. (4) Generator uses these as source material alongside Coda notes and backtest reports.",
        "details": "",
        "testStrategy": "",
