      {
        "id": "28",
        "title": "Content A/B Testing Framework",
        "description": "Build infrastructure for A/B testing content. From month 3+ when enough data exists, test the same topic with two different hooks to measure which performs better. Implementation: (1) Generator creates variant pairs â€” same topic, different hook style (e.g., fear vs. aspiration hook). (2) Tag variants in the draft system so they can be tracked as pairs. (3) Analytics dashboard compares variant performance after 48-72 hours. (4) Winning hook style gets weighted higher in future generation. Start simple: just track which hook styles perform best per pillar per platform.",
        "details": "",
        "testStrategy": "",
        "status": "deferred",
        "dependencies": [],
        "priority": "low",
