        "title": "Phase 1: LangGraph skeleton — core agent pipeline",
        "description": "Build the LangGraph content pipeline that replaces single-API-call content generation. Install langgraph + langchain-google-genai. Create scripts/agents/ package with pipeline.py (graph definition), profile_node.py (scrape user profiles weekly via Playwright), research_node.py (webcrawler search + company links + past performance), draft_node.py (per-platform Gemini generation with research + profile + brand voice), quality_node.py (validate against content-templates.md, score 0-100), decision_node.py (route to post or review queue), post node (reuse existing post_to_* functions). Wire into campaign_runner.py behind feature flag. Extend local_db.py with 4 agent tables (agent_user_profile, agent_research, agent_draft, agent_content_insights). All nodes are independent stateless functions — split-ready for server deployment later. See docs/AGENT_PIPELINE_PLAN.md.",
